Rating: 1
The colors of this dessert are beautiful, as described. However, the taste was not. The cranberries were way too tart in contrast to the mild base. Maybe some additional sugar or fewer berries or chopping the berries would have helped? It was also quite runny, so it made a mess when the sides of the springform pan were removed. My candy thermometer did not register as low as 175 degrees, so I overcooked the egg mixture and it did not fully incorporate into the other ingredients. A description of the desired consistency in the recipe would have helped to avoid that problem. It did not impact the flavor or texture much, just made little yellow spots in the white base. The base was good, but not sweet or heavy enough to counteract the extreme tartness of the cranberries. The crust was tasty, but very hard when frozen, making cutting the thing difficult. I could not get my white chocolate to curl, so must have bought the wrong kind. (I was very careful to catch it at just the right coolness. I didn't know there were different kinds of white chocolate.) Next time, I'll make cheesecake if I want cranberries on top. That could counteract the tart flavor better. This dessert would be much better with blueberries or cherries on top, although not as festive looking.

