Rating: 0
To MQuintana from Miami, FL: Some ideas...next time, make certain that your egg yolk-sugar mixture has reached 175 for safety and thickening purposes. Beat the yolks slowly for even more than 5 min. if necessary until the mixture becomes very thick and cool. This will help a lot. Start the next step by whipping the cream alone until soft peaks begin to form, then fold in the sour cream, yolk mixture, etc. It sounds like the cream mixture was overbeaten in an attempt to get it to set up.

